label: Algorithm options
definition: Options for the chosen optimization algorithm

label: Cache File Path
definition: Path for the cache file id the option cache type is set to Hdf5Cache

label: Cache Type
definition: Type of cache in GEMS (could be simple, full memory or stored in a Hdf5 file

label: Chain Linearize Option
definition: Linearize the chain of execution, if True, Otherwise, linearize the oveall MDA with base class method

label: Debug Mode
definition: Expert Debug Mode Option to test your process

label: Differentiation Method
definition: Differentiation Method for the optimizer to compute needed gradients to find the optimum, finite differences and complex step impose the choice of differentiation, user let MDA or discipline parameters choose the linearize method.

label: Samples
definition: scenarii samples

label: Zero Definition
definition: Define the value of the zero in the MDA in order to converge MDA loops

label: Equality Constraints
definition: Equality constraints in the optimization problem formulation

label: Evaluated Inputs
definition: Inputs to evaluate for the analysis (Sensitivity, Gradient, FORM ...)

label: Jacobian Evaluation
definition: If True, and Evaluation mode is True, evaluate also the jacobian of the functions of the optimization problem

label: Evaluation Mode
definition: If True, functions (constraints and objective) of the optimization problem are evaluated with values from the design space

label: Evaluated Outputs
definition: Outputs to evaluate for the analysis (Sensitivity, Gradient, FORM ...)

label: Gradient Results
definition: Results of the Gradient Analysis

label: Inequality constraints
definition: Equality constraints in the optimization problem formulation

label: MDA Max nb of iterations
definition: Maximum number of iterations for the Multi-disciplinary Design Analysis

label: Number of Processes
definition: Number of Processes used for this node

label: Objective Function
definition: Objective function of the optimization problem

label: Parallel Options
definition: Parallel options of the optimization problem

label: List of Products
definition: List of Products

label: Repository of subprocesses
definition: Folder root of the sub processes to be nested inside the DoE. If 'None' then it uses the sos_processes python for doe creation.

label: Input Samples Data
definition: Samples of the evaluated inputs

label: Output Samples Data
definition: Samples of the evaluated outputs

label: Algo of sampling
definition: Method of defining the sampling input dataset for the variable chosen in 'eval_inputs'

label: Sub MDA Class
definition: The class to instantiate for sub Multi-disciplinary Design Analysis

label: Folder name of the subprocess
definition: Selected process folder name to be nested inside the DoE.If 'None' then it uses the sos_processes python for doe creation.

label: Tolerance
definition: Tolerance of the iterative direct coupling solver, norm of the current residuals divided by initial residuals norm shall be lower than the tolerance to stop iterating

label: Use LU factorization
definition: if True, when using adjoint/forward differenciation, store a LU factorization of the matrix to solve faster multiple RHS problem

label: Usecase of the subprocess
definition: Usecase of the subprocess

label: Variation List
definition: List of variations for the sensitivity analysis

label: Warm Start
definition: If True the MDA starts with the result of the last executed MDA (really useful to compute gradient of MDA in finite differences for example)

label: Ending year
definition: Final year of the study

label: Starting year
definition: Initial year of the study
